<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Coward2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Coward,</orth> adj., destitute of courage, basely timid: <cit><quote>thy c. heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1024" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1024</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the c. captive,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 75" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 75</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the c. conquest of a wretch's knife,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 74.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 74, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.69" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 6, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.307" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 307</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.179" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.4.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 4, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 3, 25</bibl>. <cit><quote>some, turned c. but by example,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 3, 35</bibl></cit>.
